WARRI – The Olü of Warri, His Majesty Ogiame Atuwatse IIl has rebutted a statement claiming endorsement of the Bola Ahmed Tinubu. The palace of the Olu of Warri also restated that Ogiame had no political affiliation or preferred political candidate for any office in the forthcoming 2023 elections, be it at the regional, sub-national or national level The palace said this in a statement signed by Mr Oriiz U, Onuwaje, Head, Back Office Operations, Office of Ogiame Atúwatse III, the Olu of Warri, on Saturday. According to the statement, “On the instructions of His Majesty Ogiame Atuwatse IIl, the Olü of Warri, firmly rebut the statement claiming Ogiamė’s endorsement of Asiwaju Bola Ahmed Tinubu and restates that Ogiame has no political affiliation or preferred political candidate for any office in the forthcoming 2023 elections be it at the regional, sub-national or national level. “Ogiame is a father figure to all and has no personal favourite or special interests in any candidate or political party vying for any office in the forthcoming elections one way or another and will therefore not endorse or discredit any candidate to the detriment or advantage of others. “The headlines credited to Ogiame in the referenced quotes have been taken out of context and reworked to suit a specific narrative. They cannot be further from the truth.”